Greetings. He doen't usually write for rolling stone. He just contributed to Rolling stone encyclopedia of popular music by writing short essay on Prince with ratings of all his albums. Here is link to text: http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/prince/biography

item.title: By: Eric Greenwood
item.dc:creator: Eric Greenwood
item.description: i don't read rolling stone. but i think the batman soundtrack is better than several of prince's afterthought releases in the '90s. The Vault (old friends 4 sale) and Chaos and Disorder, for example.
